There's something weird going on with the unauthorized error pages for Team Shortcuts. I suspect the problem may be more wide spread.

*To reproduce:*

1. Start JIRA — {{./jmake debug}}
2. Browse to the Team Shortcuts of a non-existant project — http://localhost:8090/jira/plugins/servlet/custom-content-links-admin?entityKey=does-not-exist

*Proof that it's double encoding:*

{{curl --header 'Accept-Encoding: gzip' http://localhost:8090/jira/plugins/servlet/custom-content-links-admin?entityKey=A-REAL-PROJECT-KEY | gunzip --stdout | gunzip --stdout}}

(replace {{A-REAL-PROJECT-KEY}} with … a real project key)

*Clues:*

1. Investigate {{jira-components/jira-webapp/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/web.xml:450}}:

{code}
<!-- gzip *must* be before UrlRewriteFilter as the rewrite filter sends 'forwards' -->
<filter-mapping>
    <filter-name>gzip</filter-name>
    <url-pattern>/*</url-pattern>
    <dispatcher>REQUEST</dispatcher>
    <dispatcher>ERROR</dispatcher>
</filter-mapping>
{code}

2. Have a look at the {{GzipFilter.java:47}}:

{code}
public void doFilter(ServletRequest req, ServletResponse res, FilterChain chain) throws IOException, ServletException
{
    if (req.getAttribute(ALREADY_FILTERED) == null)
    {
        doFilterInternal(req, res, chain);
    }
    else
    {
        chain.doFilter(req, res);
    }
}
{code}

